{"session_id": 57, "bill_id": 19460, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1044, "bill_title": "revise certain provisions regarding the refund procedures for a purchaser who seeks a return of over-collected sales or use taxes from a seller.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Department of Revenue and Regulation", "Sales Tax", "Taxes"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hta05hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hta05hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hta05hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hta05hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hta05hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-20T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hou07hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-20T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hou07hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2005-01-20T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2005/hou07hb1044a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 19460, "bill_version_id": 102637, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2005-01-08T12:56:57-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to revise certain provisions regarding the refund procedures for a purchaser who seeks a return of over-collected sales or use taxes from a seller. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-59 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No purchaser has a cause of action against a seller for over-collected sales or use taxes until the purchaser has provided written notice to a seller and the seller has had sixty days to respond. The notice to the seller shall contain the information necessary to determine the validity of the request. Section 2. That chapter 10-59 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: In connection with a purchaser's written notice to a seller of over-collected sales or use taxes pursuant to section 1 of this Act, a seller is presumed to have a reasonable business practice, if in the collection of such sales or use taxes, the seller uses either a provider or a system, including a proprietary system, that is certified by the state or the Streamlined Sales Tax Governing Board; and has remitted to the state all taxes collected less any deductions, credits, or collection allowances."}, {"bill_id": 19460, "bill_version_id": 102844, "bill_version": "House Taxation Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2005-01-18T15:25:33-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to revise certain provisions regarding the refund procedures for a purchaser who seeks a return of over-collected sales or use taxes from a seller. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-59 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No purchaser has a cause of action against a seller for over-collected sales or use taxes until the purchaser has provided written notice to a seller requesting a refund of over-collected sales or use taxes and the seller has had sixty days to respond. The notice to the seller shall contain the information necessary to determine the validity of the request. Section 2. That chapter 10-59 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: In connection with a purchaser's written notice to a seller requesting a refund of over- collected sales or use taxes pursuant to section 1 of this Act, a seller is presumed to have a reasonable business practice, if in the collection of such sales or use taxes, the seller uses either a provider or a system, including a proprietary system, that is certified by the state or the Streamlined Sales Tax Governing Board; and has remitted to the state all taxes collected less any deductions, credits, or collection allowances."}, {"bill_id": 19460, "bill_version_id": 103772, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2005-02-01T09:44:44-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 19460, "action_date": "2005-01-11T12:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 102709, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/102709.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 21, "committee_id_action": 860, "committee_id_assigned": 856, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 19460, "action_date": "2005-01-18T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 102819, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/102819.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 856, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 19460, "action_date": "2005-01-18T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 102819, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/102819.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass Amended,", "journal_page": 79, "committee_id_action": 856, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 59712, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [3159, 3167, 3174, 3181, 3191, 3209, 3222, 3225, 3246, 3248, 3253, 3203, 3254], "Excused": [3178, 3249]}}, {"bill_id": 19460, "action_date": "2005-01-20T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 102961, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/102961.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass Amended,", "journal_page": 113, "committee_id_